  "prompt": "Is there any law in India to secretly report child labour?",
  "response": "In India, there are several laws and mechanisms to report child labor:\n\n1. Legal Framework:\n- Child Labor (Prohibition and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2016\n- Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015\n- Right to Education Act, 2009\n\n2. Reporting Mechanisms:\n- Childline 1098: A national helpline for reporting child labor and abuse\n- Police helpline (100)\n- Child Welfare Committees\n- NGOs working against child labor\n\n3. Anonymous Reporting Options:\n- You can report child labor anonymously through:\n- Childline 1098 helpline\n- Online child labor reporting portals\n- Local police stations\n- Child welfare organizations\n\n4. Protection for Reporters:\n- Legal provisions protect informants from any potential harassment\n- Reports can be made without revealing personal identity\n\n5. Penalties for Child Labor:\n- Imprisonment up to 2 years\n- Monetary fine\n- Stricter penalties for hazardous work\n\nWhile these mechanisms exist, it's recommended to provide as much detail as possible when reporting to help authorities take effective action.\n\nFor immediate assistance, contact Childline 1098 or local authorities.",
